fobox football league season\n| competition      = Macedonian First League\n| season           = 2000\u201301\n| winners          = [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]<br />3rd domestic title\n| relegated        = [[FK Sasa|Sasa]]<br />[[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]]<br />[[FK Borec|Borec]]<br />[[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]]\n| continentalcup1  = [[2001\u201302 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2001\u201302 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]]<br />[[FK Pelister|Pelister]]\n| continentalcup3  = [[2001 UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| league topscorer = [[Argjend Beqiri]]<br />(27 goals)\n| dates            = 20 August 2000 \u2013<br /> 27 May 2001\n| biggest home win = [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] 10\u20130 [[FK Borec|Borec]]\n| biggest away win = [[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]] 0\u20137 [[FK Pelister|Pelister]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] 10\u20130 [[FK Borec|Borec]]\n| matches          = 182\n| total goals      = 595\n| prevseason = [[1999\u20132000 Macedonian First Football League|1999\u20132000]]\n| nextseason = [[2001\u201302 Macedonian First Football League|2001\u201302]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2000\u201301 Macedonian First League''' was the 9th season of the [[Macedonian First Football League]], the highest [[Association football|football]] league of [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]. The first matches of the season were played on 20 August 2000 and the last on 27 May 2001. [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]] defended their championship title, having won their third title in a row. Due to the change of the league structure (the league was reduced to 12 clubs from the following season), the bottom four teams were relegated.\n\n== Promotion and relegation ==\n{|style=\"border:0;width:69%;\"\n|-style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n|\n; At the start of the 2000\u201301 season\nPromoted from [[1999\u20132000 Macedonian Second Football League|1999\u20132000 Second League]]\n* [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija HB]] (Winners; West)\n* [[FK Belasica|Belasica]] (Winners; East)\nRelegated to [[2000\u201301 Macedonian Second Football League|2000\u201301 Second League]]\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (13th)\n* [[FK Kumanovo|Kumanovo]] (14th)\n\n|\n; At the end of the 2000\u201301 season\nPromoted from [[2000\u201301 Macedonian Second Football League|2000\u201301 Second League]]\n* [[FK Kumanovo|Kumanovo]] (Winners)\n* [[FK Napredok|Napredok]] (Runners-up)\nRelegated to [[2001\u201302 Macedonian Second Football League|2001\u201302 Second League]]\n* [[FK Sasa|Sasa]] (11th)\n* [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija HB]] (12th)\n* [[FK Borec|Borec MHK]] (13th)\n* [[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]] (14th)\n|}\n\n== Participating teams ==\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in '''2000\u201301 Macedonian First League'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=21.433333 |label='''Skopje'''  |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.72     |long=21.793333 |label=[[FK Borec|Borec]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.031944 |long=21.334722 |label=[[FK Pelister|Pelister]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.35     |long=21.55     |label=[[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.916667 |long=22.416667 |label=[[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.019722 |long=22.591667 |label=[[FK Sasa|Sasa]] |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.433333 |long=22.633333 |label=[[FK Belasica|Belasica]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.066667 |long=22.183333 |label=[[FK Sileks|Sileks]] }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.433333 |long=22        |label=[[GFK Tikvesh|Tikvesh]] |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42        |long=20.966666 |label=[[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija]] |position=bottom}}\n<!--HIDDEN MARKER FOR SKOPJE CLUBS (UPPER RIGHT CORNER)-->\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.44 |long=23.2 |label='''Skopje&nbsp;clubs:'''|position=left | outside  = 1 <!-- Turn off error category due to location outside map-->}}\n{{Location map~ |Republic of Macedonia|mark=TransparentPlaceholder.png|lat=42.36 |long=23.2 |label=[[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica]]<br>[[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija]]<br>[[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki]]<br>[[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]<br>[[FK Vardar|Vardar]] |position=left| outside  = 1 <!-- Turn off error category due to location outside map--> }}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Club\n! City\n! Stadium\n|-\n| [[FK Belasica|Belasica Geras Cunev]]\n| [[Strumica]]\n| [[Stadion Blagoj Istatov|Stadion Mladost]]\n|-\n| [[FK Borec|Borec MHK]]\n| [[Veles, North Macedonia|Veles]]\n| Gradski stadion Veles\n|-\n| [[FK Cementarnica 55|Cementarnica 55]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[Stadion Cementarnica]]\n|-\n| [[FK Makedonija Gjor\u010de Petrov|Makedonija Asiba]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[Gjor\u010de Petrov Stadium|Stadion Gjorche Petrov]]\n|-\n| [[FK Osogovo|Osogovo]]\n| [[Ko\u010dani|Kochani]]\n| [[Stadion Nikola Mantov]]\n|-\n| [[FK Pelister|Pelister]]\n| [[Bitola]]\n| [[Stadion Tumbe Kafe]]\n|-\n| [[FK Pobeda|Pobeda]]\n| [[Prilep]]\n| [[Stadion Goce Del\u010dev|Stadion Goce Delchev]]\n|-\n| [[FK Rabotni\u010dki|Rabotnichki Kometal]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[To\u0161e Proeski Arena|Gradski stadion Skopje]]\n|-\n| [[FK Sasa|Sasa]]\n| [[Makedonska Kamenica]]\n| Gradski stadion Makedonska Kamenica\n|-\n| [[KF Shk\u00ebndija|Shk\u00ebndija HB]]\n| [[Tetovo]]\n| [[Ecolog Arena|Gradski stadion Tetovo]]\n|-\n| [[FK Sileks|Sileks]]\n| [[Kratovo, North Macedonia|Kratovo]]\n| [[Gradski stadion Kratovo|Stadion Sileks]]\n|-\n| [[FK Sloga Jugomagnat|Sloga Jugomagnat]]\n| [[Skopje]]\n| [[\