{"title_page": "Chase Young", "text_new": "{{short description|American football defensive end}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{About|the American football player|the Xiaolin Showdown character|Chase Young (Xiaolin Showdown)}}\n<!-- DO NOT ADD BEFORE THE 2020 NFL DRAFT\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Chase Young\n| image               =\n| alt                 =\n| caption             =\n| number              = --\n| current_team        =\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1999|4|14}}\n| birth_place         = [[Upper Marlboro, Maryland]]\n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 5\n| weight_lb           = 265\n| high_school         = [[DeMatha Catholic High School|DeMatha Catholic]] ([[Hyattsville, Maryland]])\n| college             = [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]]\n| draftyear           = 2020\n| draftround          =\n| draftpick           =\n| undraftedyear       =\n| pastteams           =\n* [[]] ({{NFL Year|2020}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Unsigned draft pick\n| highlights          =\n* [[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]] (2019)\n* [[Chuck Bednarik Award]] (2019)\n* [[Ted Hendricks Award]] (2019)\n* [[Chicago Tribune Silver Football]] (2019)\n* [[Nagurski\u2013Woodson Defensive Player of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Smith\u2013Brown Defensive Lineman of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Unanimous All-American]] ([[2019 College Football All-America Team|2019]])\n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          =\n| statweek            =\n| statlabel1          = [[Tackle (football move)|Tackles]]\n| statvalue1          = 0\n| statlabel2          = [[Quarterback sack|Sacks]]\n| statvalue2          = 0\n| statlabel3          = [[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n| statvalue3          = 0\n| statlabel4          = [[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n| statvalue4          = 0\n| nflnew              =\n| pfr                 =\n}}\n-->\n{{Infobox college football player\n|name=Chase Young\n|school=Ohio State Buckeyes\n|currentnumber=2\n|major=[[Criminology]]\n|currentposition=[[Defensive end]]\n|class=Junior\n|bowlgames=\n* [[2017 Cotton Bowl Classic (December)]]\n* [[2019 Rose Bowl]]\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1999|4|14}}\n|birth_place=[[Upper Marlboro, Maryland]]\n|heightft=6\n|heightin=5\n|weight_lb=265\n|highschool=[[DeMatha Catholic High School|DeMatha Catholic]] ([[Hyattsville, Maryland]])\n|pastschools=\n* [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]] (2017\u20132019)\n|espn=4241986\n|highlights=\n* [[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]] (2019)\n* [[Chuck Bednarik Award]] (2019)\n* [[Ted Hendricks Award]] (2019)\n* [[Chicago Tribune Silver Football]] (2019)\n* [[Nagurski\u2013Woodson Defensive Player of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Smith\u2013Brown Defensive Lineman of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Unanimous All-American]] ([[2019 College Football All-America Team|2019]])\n* First-team All-Big Ten ([[2019 Big Ten Conference football season#All-Conference Teams|2019]])\n* Second-team All-Big Ten ([[2018 Big Ten Conference football season#All-Conference Teams|2018]])\n* Second-team ''USA Today'' High School All-American ([[2016 USA Today All-USA high school football team|2016]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[Walter Camp Award]] National Player of the Week\n}}\n'''Chase Young''' (born April 14, 1999) is an [[American football]] [[defensive end]]. He played college football at [[Ohio State University]], playing for the [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Buckeyes]] from 2017\u20132019. He ranks second all-time there in career sacks with 30.5, and holds their single-season sack record with 16.5, doing so in his final season. His performance that year won him several honors, such as the [[Chuck Bednarik Award]], [[Ted Hendricks Award]], and [[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]], as well as being named a [[Heisman Trophy]] finalist and unanimous [[All-America]]n.\n\n==Early life==\nChase Young was born in [[Upper Marlboro, Maryland]] on April 14, 1999.<ref name=\"OSUBio\">{{cite web |title=Chase Young - Football |url=https://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/roster/chase-young/ |website=OhioStateBuckeyes.com |access-date=December 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213232426/https://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/roster/chase-young/ |archive-date=December 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chase Young Walter Camp National Defensive PoW \u2026 Again! |url=https://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/chase-young-walter-camp-national-defensive-pow-again/ |website=OhioStateBuckeyes.com |accessdate=February 26, 2020}}</ref> He began playing American football as a child, later attending [[St. Vincent Pallotti High School]] in [[Laurel, Maryland]] as a freshman in 2013, where he started at [[quarterback]] and [[outside linebacker]] before switching to defensive end later that year.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wiltfong |first1=Steve |title=The Chase for Young is on |url=https://247sports.com/Article/Touted-DE-Chase-Young-talks-Buckeyes-Maryland-Alabama-USC-44894899/ |website=247 Sports |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704181213/http://247sports.com/Article/Touted-DE-Chase-Young-talks-Buckeyes-Maryland-Alabama-USC-44894899 |archive-date=July 4, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Santoliquito |first1=Joseph |title=Eagles fan Chase Young may soon become an Eagles\u2019 nightmare |url=https://www.phillyvoice.com/chase-young-philadelphia-eagles-fan-ohio-state-maxwell-awards-nfl-draft-washington-redskins/ |website=Philly Voice |accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> As a sophomore the following year, he and the team won the MIAA C conference championship.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Worgo |first1=Tom |title=Pallotti football relies on running game, defense to defeat AACS for MIAA C Conference title |url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/maryland/laurel/ph-ll-pallott-annapolisareachristianschool-footballi-story.html |website=Baltimore Sun |accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref> He was also a member of the school's choir, playing the piano, saxophone, and violin.<ref name=\"Dayton\">{{cite web |last1=Archdeacon |first1=Tom |title=Archdeacon: Ohio State\u2019s Young a menace in mauling of Badgers |url=https://www.daytondailynews.com/sports/archdeacon-ohio-state-young-menace-mauling-badgers/U1tD5O9xjhQ7MBTEC9lc4J/ |website=Dayton Daily News |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he transferred to [[DeMatha Catholic High School]] in [[Hyattsville, Maryland]]. As a senior in 2016, he had 118 tackles with 19 sacks, which helped the team go undefeated and win the state championship.<ref name=\"SportingNews\">{{cite web |last1=Bender |first1=Bill |title=The making of Chase Young: How an athletic freak at Ohio State became the best player in the NFL Draft |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/chase-young-ohio-state-best-player-nfl-draft/1bek45kwrzjmq12eh3jt0xre9g |website=Sporting News |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303052838/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/chase-young-ohio-state-best-player-nfl-draft/1bek45kwrzjmq12eh3jt0xre9g |archive-date=March 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was recognized one of the best high school football players in the nation, where he was included on the [[2016 USA Today All-USA high school football team]], as well as being named as the all-metropolitan defensive football player of the year by the ''[[Washington Post]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Halley |first1=Jim |title=ALL-USA Football Defense: Second Team |url=https://usatodayhss.com/2016/2016-american-family-insurance-all-usa-football-defense-second-team |website=usatodayhss.com |publisher=USA Today |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202012103/http://usatodayhss.com/2016/2016-american-family-insurance-all-usa-football-defense-second-team |archive-date=February 2, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=2016 Fall All-Met |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/2016-fall-allmet/ |website=Washington Post |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626021033/https://www.washingtonpost.com/2016-fall-allmet/ |archive-date=June 26, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was also invited to the [[International Bowl presented by USA Football|International Bowl]] and [[All-American Bowl (high school football)|All-American Bowl]], playing on the East team for the latter.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lind |first1=Andrew |title=The Hurry Up: Ohio State Makes Cut for Four-Star Texas Safety and Commit Caps High School Career With State Championship |url=https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football-recruiting/2016/12/78253/the-hurry-up-ohio-state-jordan-moore-top-10-wyatt-davis-state-championship |website=Eleven Warriors |accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=DeMatha defensive end Chase Young solidifies standing with Army All-American selection |url=https://usatodayhss.com/2016/dematha-defensive-end-chase-young-solidifies-standing-with-army-all-american-selection |website=usatodayhss.com |publisher=USA Today |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221142657/http://usatodayhss.com/2016/dematha-defensive-end-chase-young-solidifies-standing-with-army-all-american-selection/ |archive-date=December 21, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Young also played basketball for both schools, where he was a DeMatha teammate and friend of future [[NBA]] player [[Markelle Fultz]], who was [[List of first overall NBA draft picks|selected first overall]] in the [[2017 NBA Draft]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thamel |first1=Pete |title=Ohio State DE Chase Young chasing top draft pick of HS basketball teammate Markelle Fultz |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/ohio-state-de-chase-young-chasing-top-draft-pick-of-high-school-basketball-teammate-markelle-fultz-024346344.html |website=Yahoo Sports |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228192302/https://sports.yahoo.com/ohio-state-de-chase-young-chasing-top-draft-pick-of-high-school-basketball-teammate-markelle-fultz-024346344.html |archive-date=February 28, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nYoung received scholarship offers from over 40 colleges before committing to [[Ohio State University]] in July 2016, choosing them over other schools such as [[University of Alabama|Alabama]] and [[University of Maryland, College Park|Maryland]] due to their approach that he felt was more \"family-oriented\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Connors |first1=Ryan |title=5-star DE Chase Young commits to Ohio State: Maryland football misses out on top local prospect |url=https://www.testudotimes.com/2016/7/22/12261298/maryland-football-recruiting-chase-young-commits-ohio-state |website=testudotimes.com |accessdate=March 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030181151/http://www.testudotimes.com/2016/7/22/12261298/maryland-football-recruiting-chase-young-commits-ohio-state |archive-date=October 30, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lombardi |first1=Matt |title=Chase Young Explains Why He Chose Ohio State Over Alabama |url=https://thespun.com/big-ten/ohio-state-buckeyes/chase-young-explains-why-he-chose-ohio-state-over-alabama |website=The Spun |accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref> As a freshman in 2017, Young recorded 3.5 sacks as a rotational player.<ref name=\"Sophomore\">{{cite web |last1=Ludwiczak |first1=Brett |title=Ohio State defensive end Chase Young is ready to build off a breakout sophomore season |url=https://www.landgrantholyland.com/2019/1/17/18186858/ohio-state-news-football-chase-young-jonathon-cooper-zach-harrison-womens-basketball-kevin-mcguff |website=Land Grant Holy Land |accessdate=May 10, 2019 |date=January 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510191344/https://www.landgrantholyland.com/2019/1/17/18186858/ohio-state-news-football-chase-young-jonathon-cooper-zach-harrison-womens-basketball-kevin-mcguff |archive-date=May 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> During his sophomore season in 2018, Young sprained both ankles but still managed to record 10.5 sacks on the season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haas-Hill |first1=Colin |title=K.J. Hill, Chase Young and J.K. Dobbins Could Break or Tie Ohio State Individual Records in 2019 |url=https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football/2019/05/104153/ohio-state-individual-records-in-jeopardy-of-being-broken-next-season |website=Eleven Warriors |accessdate=May 10, 2019 |date=May 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510191351/https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football/2019/05/104153/ohio-state-individual-records-in-jeopardy-of-being-broken-next-season |archive-date=May 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> He began to play more after fellow defensive end [[Nick Bosa]] was injured in the latter part of the season, recording three sacks in the [[2018 Big Ten Football Championship Game]] against [[Northwestern Wildcats football|Northwestern]].<ref name=\"Sophomore\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Rowland |first1=Kyle |title=Ohio State defensive end Chase Young wants to be the best |url=https://www.toledoblade.com/sports/ohio-state/2018/10/10/ohio-state-buckeyes-football-chase-young-wants-to-be-the-best/stories/20181009108 |website=[[Toledo Blade]] |accessdate=May 10, 2019 |date=October 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510205559/https://www.toledoblade.com/sports/ohio-state/2018/10/10/ohio-state-buckeyes-football-chase-young-wants-to-be-the-best/stories/20181009108 |archive-date=May 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring his junior season in 2019, Young tied Ohio State school records for single-game sacks (four) and tackles for loss (five) in a win against [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Planos |first1=Josh |title=Ohio State's Chase Young Is Playing Like A Heisman Contender |url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/ohio-states-chase-young-is-playing-like-a-heisman-contender/ |website=FiveThirtyEight |publisher=ABC News Internet Ventures |accessdate=November 14, 2019 |date=October 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116060500/https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/ohio-states-chase-young-is-playing-like-a-heisman-contender/ |archive-date=November 16, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Heisman Watch: Chase Young Crashes Quarterback Party |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/page/HeismanWatch191029/heisman-watch-chase-young-crashes-quarterback-party |website=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=November 14, 2019 |date=October 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031175718/https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/page/HeismanWatch191029/heisman-watch-chase-young-crashes-quarterback-party |archive-date=October 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hummer |first1=Chris |title=Chase Young is on a historic, Heisman-worthy pace |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Chase-Young-Heisman-Trophy-Ohio-State-football-2020-NFL-Draft-137613670/ |website=[[247Sports.com]] |accessdate=November 14, 2019 |date=October 28, 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, Young was suspended for two games by the [[NCAA]] for getting an unauthorized loan from a family friend to allegedly help his girlfriend attend the [[2019 Rose Bowl]], which he later repaid in full.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bumbaca |first1=Chris |title=Ohio State Buckeyes' Chase Young expected to serve four-game suspension, per reports |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/ncaaf/bigten/2019/11/09/chase-young-suspension-ohio-state-expects-heisman-out-4-games/2543764001/ |website=USA Today |accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Shook |first1=Nick |title=NCAA rules Ohio State's Chase Young to miss 1 more game |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001076478/article/ncaa-rules-ohio-states-chase-young-to-miss-1-more-game |website=NFL.com |accessdate=November 13, 2019 |date=November 13, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113185829/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001076478/article/ncaa-rules-ohio-states-chase-young-to-miss-1-more-game |archive-date=November 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Young recorded three sacks against Penn State in his first game after returning.<ref name=\"SportingNews\"/> He ended the season with 16.5 sacks, 46 tackles, six forced fumbles, three passes batted down, and a blocked field goal.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rapp |first1=Timothy |title=Chase Young Rumors: Teams Behind Lions in 2020 NFL Draft Haven't Contacted Star |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2885639-chase-young-rumors-teams-behind-lions-in-2020-nfl-draft-havent-contacted-star |website=Bleacher Report |accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Noga |first1=Joe |title=Chase Young, Ohio State DE: 2020 NFL Draft profile |url=https://www.cleveland.com/browns/2020/03/chase-young-ohio-state-de-2020-nfl-draft-profile.html |website=Cleveland.com |access-date=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331014816/https://www.cleveland.com/browns/2020/03/chase-young-ohio-state-de-2020-nfl-draft-profile.html |archive-date=March 31, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> His 16.5 sacks broke the single-season school record previously held by [[Vernon Gholston]], who had 14 in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kaufman |first1=Joey |title=Chase Young a Heisman finalist despite playing defense, being suspended |url=https://www.buckeyextra.com/sports/20191213/ohio-state-football--chase-young-heisman-finalist-despite-playing-defense-being-suspended |website=Buckeyextra.com |publisher=The Columbus Dispatch |accessdate=December 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224230059/https://www.buckeyextra.com/sports/20191213/ohio-state-football--chase-young-heisman-finalist-despite-playing-defense-being-suspended |archive-date=December 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nYoung won several awards and honors for his performance that season, including the [[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]],<ref name=\"Bronko\">{{cite web |last1=Straka |first1=Dean |title=Ohio State DE Chase Young wins Bronko Nagurski Trophy |url=https://247sports.com/Article/ohio-state-defensive-end-chase-young-wins-2019-bronko-nagurski-trophy-140221610/ |website=247 Sports |accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> [[Chuck Bednarik Award]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Chase Young Wins 2019 Chuck Bednarik Award |url=https://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/chase-young-wins-2019-bednarik-award/ |website=OhioStateBuckeyes.com |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103195746/https://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/chase-young-wins-2019-bednarik-award/ |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Ted Hendricks Award]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clay |first1=Jarrod |title=Chase Young wins 2019 Ted Hendricks Award |url=https://abc6onyourside.com/sports/the-football-fever/chase-young-wins-2019-ted-hendricks-award |website=ABC 6 |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103195619/https://abc6onyourside.com/sports/the-football-fever/chase-young-wins-2019-ted-hendricks-award |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Chicago Tribune Silver Football]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Greenstein |first1=Teddy |title=Chase Young is the 2019 Chicago Tribune Silver Football winner \u2014 and the 1st Ohio State defensive player to win the award in its 95-year history |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/college/ct-chase-young-ohio-state-silver-football-20191206-imh2o6cs45cpdbj5e7b7sla4zu-story.html |website=Chicago Tribune |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230142145/https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/college/ct-chase-young-ohio-state-silver-football-20191206-imh2o6cs45cpdbj5e7b7sla4zu-story.html |archive-date=December 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Nagurski\u2013Woodson Defensive Player of the Year]],<ref name=\"Bronko\"/> and [[Smith\u2013Brown Defensive Lineman of the Year]].<ref name=\"Bronko\"/> In addition, he was twice named the [[Walter Camp Award|Walter Camp]] defensive player of the week for his performances against Wisconsin and Penn State,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hass-Hill |first1=Colin |title=Chase Young Named Walter Camp National Defensive Player Of The Week For Second Time This Season |url=https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football/2019/11/109337/chase-young-named-walter-camp-national-defensive-player-of-the-week-for-second-time-this-season |website=Elevan Warriors |accessdate=March 9, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127222424/https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football/2019/11/109337/chase-young-named-walter-camp-national-defensive-player-of-the-week-for-second-time-this-season |archive-date=November 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and was [[List of unanimous All-Americans in college football|unanimously named]] to the 2019 All-Big Ten and [[2019 College Football All-America Team|All-America Teams]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Big Ten Announces Football All-Conference Teams for Defense and Special Teams and Select Individual Honors |url=https://bigten.org/news/2019/12/3/big-ten-announces-football-all-conference-teams-for-defense-and-special-teams-and-select-individual-honors.aspx |website=BigTen.org |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204022652/https://bigten.org/news/2019/12/3/big-ten-announces-football-all-conference-teams-for-defense-and-special-teams-and-select-individual-honors.aspx |archive-date=December 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was also named a finalist for the [[Maxwell Award]] and [[Heisman Trophy]], becoming only the ninth defensive player since 1982 to be nominated for the latter, where he finished fourth in voting behind quarterbacks [[Joe Burrow]], [[Jalen Hurts]], and [[Justin Fields]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Duffley |first1=John |title=Joe Burrow Wins Maxwell Award as CFB\u2019s Player of the Year |url=https://fanbuzz.com/college-football/maxwell-award-watch-list/ |website=FanBuzz.com |accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Cross |first1=Ian |title=OSU defensive end Chase Young declares for 2020 NFL Draft |url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/sports/college-sports/osu/osu-defensive-end-chase-young-declares-for-2020-nfl-draft |website=News 5 Cleveland |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104141151/https://www.news5cleveland.com/sports/college-sports/osu/osu-defensive-end-chase-young-declares-for-2020-nfl-draft |archive-date=January 4, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=ESPN News Services |title=Bayou bliss: LSU QB Joe Burrow takes home Heisman |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/28298763/bayou-bliss-lsu-qb-joe-burrow-takes-home-heisman |website=ESPN |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230123538/https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/28298763/bayou-bliss-lsu-qb-joe-burrow-takes-home-heisman |archive-date=December 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> He finished his career at Ohio State with 30.5 total sacks, which ranks second all-time there behind [[Mike Vrabel]]'s 36.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Anders |first1=Andy |title=Football: Chase Young declares for NFL Draft |url=https://www.thelantern.com/2020/01/ohio-state-football-chase-young-declares-for-nfl-draft-2/ |website=The Latern |accessdate=March 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406225649/https://www.thelantern.com/2020/01/ohio-state-football-chase-young-declares-for-nfl-draft-2/ |archive-date=April 6, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Season\n! colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" |Games\n! colspan=4|Tackles\n! colspan=2|Sacks\n! colspan=2|Fumbles\n|-\n! Solo !! Ast !! Total !! TFL !! Total !! Yards\n!FF\n!FR\n|-\n![[2017 Ohio State Buckeyes football season|2017]]\n|9\n|11\n|7\n|18\n|5\n|3.5\n|20\n|1\n|0\n|-\n![[2018 Ohio State Buckeyes football season|2018]]\n|13\n|25\n|9\n|34\n|14.5\n|10.5\n|60\n|1\n|0\n|-\n![[2019 Ohio State Buckeyes football season|2019]]\n|12\n|32\n|14\n|46\n|21\n|16.5\n|117\n|7\n|0\n|-\n! Totals<ref>{{cite web |title=Chase Young College Stats |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/chase-young-1.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=College Football Reference |accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n!34\n!68||30||98||40.5||30.5||197\n!9\n!0\n|}\n\n==Professional career==\nYoung decided to forgo his senior year by declaring for the [[2020 NFL Draft]],<ref name=\"SportingNews\"/><ref>{{cite web |author1=ESPN |title=Ohio State DE Chase Young announces he's entering NFL draft |url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/28416265/ohio-state-de-chase-young-announces-entering-nfl-draft |website=ESPN |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103191232/https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/28416265/ohio-state-de-chase-young-announces-entering-nfl-draft |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Shook |first1=Nick |title=Ohio State DE Chase Young declares for 2020 draft |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001094141/article/ohio-state-de-chase-young-declares-for-2020-draft |website=NFL.com |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103195556/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001094141/article/ohio-state-de-chase-young-declares-for-2020-draft |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> where he is considered by many to be its best overall prospect.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Birkett |first1=Dave |title=Chase Young is NFL draft's No. 1 prospect; don't let late-season slump worry you |url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/02/24/chase-young-ohio-state-football-nfl-draft/4856539002/ |website=Detroit Free Press |accessdate=February 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225215049/https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/02/24/chase-young-ohio-state-football-nfl-draft/4856539002/ |archive-date=February 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Copeland |first1=Kareem |title=Chase Young is a \u2018generational talent\u2019 and clear choice for Redskins, draft expert says |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2020/02/22/chase-young-is-generational-talent-clear-choice-redskins-draft-expert-says/ |website=Washington Post |accessdate=February 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226103632/https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2020/02/22/chase-young-is-generational-talent-clear-choice-redskins-draft-expert-says/ |archive-date=February 26, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McAtee |first1=Riley |title=Chase Young and the Perennial Draft Appeal of an Elite Pass Rusher |url=https://www.theringer.com/nfl/2020/4/13/21218550/2020-nfl-draft-chase-young-defensive-end-prospects-trend |website=The Ringer |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> He attended the [[NFL Combine]] but did not participate in any workouts or drills, stating that he did not want to waste time being a \"combine athlete\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=DelVecchio |first1=Steve |title=Chase Young has great explanation for skipping combine workouts |url=https://www.yardbarker.com/nfl/articles/chase_young_has_great_explanation_for_skipping_combine_workouts/s1_127_31450310 |website=Yardbarker |accessdate=March 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303053338/https://www.yardbarker.com/nfl/articles/chase_young_has_great_explanation_for_skipping_combine_workouts/s1_127_31450310 |archive-date=March 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Young was one of 58 players invited to the draft, which is to be held virtually due to [[social distancing]] regulations arising from the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Around The NFL staff |title=58 prospects to virtually participate in NFL draft |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001108866/article/58-prospects-to-virtually-participate-in-nfl-draft |website=NFL.com |accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nYoung's father, Greg, played college basketball at [[Bowie State University]] before working as a police deputy in [[Arlington County, Virginia]], while his mother, Carla, works for the [[US Department of Transportation]].<ref name=\"Dayton\"/><ref name=\"Law\">{{cite web |last1=Means |first1=Stephen |title=Ohio State\u2019s star DE Chase Young following his family\u2019s formula to success: From athletics to law enforcement |url=https://www.cleveland.com/osu/2019/09/ohio-states-star-de-chase-young-following-his-familys-formula-to-success-from-athletics-to-law-enforcement.html |website=Cleveland.com |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003205731/https://www.cleveland.com/osu/2019/09/ohio-states-star-de-chase-young-following-his-familys-formula-to-success-from-athletics-to-law-enforcement.html |archive-date=October 3, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Young has a sister, Weslie, who played college basketball at [[North Carolina Wesleyan]].<ref name=\"Tattoo\">{{cite web |last1=Culpepper |first1=Chuck |title=A veteran and grandfather\u2019s kinetic tribute \u2014 on the arm of college football\u2019s best player |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2019/11/22/chase-young-grandfather-tattoo-nfl-ohio-state-college-football/ |website=Washington Post |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229110140/https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2019/11/22/chase-young-grandfather-tattoo-nfl-ohio-state-college-football/ |archive-date=December 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> At Ohio State, Young decided to major in [[criminology]] after being inspired by his father and two of his uncles, who all work in [[law enforcement]].<ref name=\"Law\"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Chase Young, DeMatha Catholic, Weak-Side Defensive End |url=https://247sports.com/Player/Chase-Young-83154/high-school-144085/ |website=[[247Sports.com]] |accessdate=May 10, 2019}}</ref> He is sometimes called the \"Predator\" for his on-field dominance, as well as his [[dreadlock]]s resembling [[Predator (fictional species)|Predators]] from the ''[[Predator (franchise)|Predator]]'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thamel |first1=Pete |title=Why freaky OSU DE Chase Young is the best player in college football: \u2018There\u2019s only 10 guys like him in the world\u2019 |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/chase-young-best-player-in-college-football-154802867.html |website=sports.yahoo.com |accessdate=April 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101104924/https://sports.yahoo.com/chase-young-best-player-in-college-football-154802867.html |archive-date=January 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hooley |first1=Bruce |title=Jackson Carman Eluded Ohio State; will Block Chase Young |url=https://www.si.com/college/ohiostate/football/jackson-carman-eluded-ohio-state-now-will-block-chase-young |website=SI.com |accessdate=April 8, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225151946/https://www.si.com/college/ohiostate/football/jackson-carman-eluded-ohio-state-now-will-block-chase-young |archive-date=December 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hooley |first1=Bruce |title=Ohio State's Chase Young May Be Better Than Bosa Brothers |url=https://www.si.com/college/ohiostate/football/ohio-states-chase-young-may-be-better-than-bosa-brothers |website=SI.com |accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> Young has a tattoo of Carl H. Robinson, his late grandfather and [[US Air Force]] veteran, on his right arm.<ref name=\"Tattoo\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{twitter|youngchase907}}\n* [https://www.nfl.com/prospects/chase-young?id=3219594f-5514-6550-d662-263c81d981b1 NFL.com prospect profile]\n* [http://ohiostatebuckeyes.com/roster/chase-young/ Ohio State Buckeyes bio]\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Chase Young|list=\n{{Ted Hendricks Award}}\n{{Bronko Nagurski Trophy}}\n{{Chuck Bednarik Award}}\n{{2019 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{Chicago Tribune Silver Football navbox}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Young, Chase}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:African-American players of American football]]\n[[Category:All-American college football players]]\n[[Category:American football defensive ends]]\n[[Category:DeMatha Catholic High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ohio State Buckeyes football players]]\n[[Category:People from Upper Marlboro, Maryland]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Maryland]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Washington metropolitan area]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football defensive end}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{About|the American football player|the Xiaolin Showdown character|Chase Young (Xiaolin Showdown)}}\n<!-- DO NOT ADD BEFORE THE 2020 NFL DRAFT\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Chase Young\n| image               =\n| alt                 =\n| caption             =\n| number              = --\n| current_team        =\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1999|4|14}}\n| birth_place         = [[Upper Marlboro, Maryland]]\n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 5\n| weight_lb           = 265\n| high_school         = [[DeMatha Catholic High School|DeMatha Catholic]] ([[Hyattsville, Maryland]])\n| college             = [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]]\n| draftyear           = 2020\n| draftround          =\n| draftpick           =\n| undraftedyear       =\n| pastteams           =\n* [[]] ({{NFL Year|2020}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Unsigned draft pick\n| highlights          =\n* [[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]] (2019)\n* [[Chuck Bednarik Award]] (2019)\n* [[Ted Hendricks Award]] (2019)\n* [[Chicago Tribune Silver Football]] (2019)\n* [[Nagurski\u2013Woodson Defensive Player of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Smith\u2013Brown Defensive Lineman of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[Unanimous